  "prompt": "Do convictions for drug crimes include alcohol as being a drug?",
  "response": "Generally, drug crime convictions focus on illegal substances like cocaine, heroin, methamphetamine, marijuana (in some jurisdictions), and prescription drugs obtained illegally. Alcohol is typically not included in drug crime statutes, as it is regulated differently. Alcohol-related offenses are usually covered under separate laws such as public intoxication, driving under the influence (DUI), and underage drinking. However, specific definitions can vary by jurisdiction, so local laws should be consulted for precise details.",
